# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: BlackMonolith | Scene: TheBlackMonolithMage7
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah was sitting behind her desk in the main study."
    new "Sarah was sitting behind her desk in the main study."

    old "Spread out on her desk, a wild mix of texts. Some selected by herself, some by Metis, some by the spirit."
    new "Spread out on her desk, a wild mix of texts. Some selected by herself, some by Metis, some by the spirit."

    old "She had spend most the day studying."
    new "She had spend most the day studying."

    old "But all minds have their limit, and Sarah could feel hers drifting."
    new "But all minds have their limit, and Sarah could feel hers drifting."

    old "The more I read the less I feel like I know."
    new "The more I read the less I feel like I know."

    old "The room was empty, no answer came. Not that she had expected any."
    new "The room was empty, no answer came. Not that she had expected any."

    old "Almost ready to retire for the night, Sarah suddenly heard a swift thomping noise."
    new "Almost ready to retire for the night, Sarah suddenly heard a swift thomping noise."

    old "The sounds came faster and harder."
    new "The sounds came faster and harder."

    old "Suddenly, like a scarlet tornado, Samayra rushed into the room."
    new "Suddenly, like a scarlet tornado, Samayra rushed into the room."

    old "Sarah! Sarah! Sarah!"
    new "Sarah! Sarah! Sarah!"

    old "The girl was almost out of breath, yet still full of energy."
    new "The girl was almost out of breath, yet still full of energy."

    old "Samayra, are you okay? Did something happen?"
    new "Samayra, are you okay? Did something happen?"

    old "Samayra looked at her confused."
    new "Samayra looked at her confused."

    old "Something happen? No!"
    new "Something happen? No!"

    old "No it's not that! I was out...outside..."
    new "No it's not that! I was out...outside..."

    old "She was still trying to catch her breath."
    new "She was still trying to catch her breath."

    old "Samayra...take a deep breath. You're gonna faint."
    new "Samayra...take a deep breath. You're gonna faint."

    old "The girl leaned against the wall and took a few deep breaths. It seemed to steady her."
    new "The girl leaned against the wall and took a few deep breaths. It seemed to steady her."

    old "Okay, I'm good."
    new "Okay, I'm good."

    old "She had a wide grin on her face as she continued."
    new "She had a wide grin on her face as she continued."

    old "So, like I was saying, I was outside, I had gone up and down the market real quick."
    new "So, like I was saying, I was outside, I had gone up and down the market real quick."

    old "Sarah didn't like the idea of the girl wandering the city of Lethram by herself. But she also could not find it in her heart to forbid her."
    new "Sarah didn't like the idea of the girl wandering the city of Lethram by herself. But she also could not find it in her heart to forbid her."

    old "All her life she had been a prisoner in a golden cage. Sarah couldn't imagine doing that to her."
    new "All her life she had been a prisoner in a golden cage. Sarah couldn't imagine doing that to her."

    old "So I was walking back up the road, and I heard this music!"
    new "So I was walking back up the road, and I heard this music!"

    old "So I went into a side road and I followed the music, and before I knew it there was this huge crowd!"
    new "So I went into a side road and I followed the music, and before I knew it there was this huge crowd!"

    old "And Sarah, there was this huge party!"
    new "And Sarah, there was this huge party!"

    old "Everyone was dancing, and drinking and they looked like they were having so much fun!"
    new "Everyone was dancing, and drinking and they looked like they were having so much fun!"

    old "Sarah watched the girl intently, her face glowing as she retold the story."
    new "Sarah watched the girl intently, her face glowing as she retold the story."

    old "The girl had stopped talking, as if she had reached the end of her story."
    new "The girl had stopped talking, as if she had reached the end of her story."

    old "Well...it happened just now! I ran home as fast as I could. It's still going!"
    new "Well...it happened just now! I ran home as fast as I could. It's still going!"

    old "We should go!"
    new "We should go!"

    old "Go out dancing with Samayra"
    new "Go out dancing with Samayra"

    old "Sarah looked at the piles of books and partially read texts."
    new "Sarah looked at the piles of books and partially read texts."

    old "She wanted to get as far away from them as possible."
    new "She wanted to get as far away from them as possible."

    old "You know what, Samayra...we can go!"
    new "You know what, Samayra...we can go!"

    old "Samayra jumped up into the air, punching with one fist."
    new "Samayra jumped up into the air, punching with one fist."

    old "Hey, calm down now. You're gonna need that energy if you wanna keep up with me."
    new "Hey, calm down now. You're gonna need that energy if you wanna keep up with me."

    old "I used to dance all day long in Bagrad, I think I'll be fine."
    new "I used to dance all day long in Bagrad, I think I'll be fine."

    old "Sarah walked up towards Samayra."
    new "Sarah walked up towards Samayra."

    old "So...you're in charge I guess. You know where the place is, right?"
    new "So...you're in charge I guess. You know where the place is, right?"

    old "Samayra excitedly nodded."
    new "Samayra excitedly nodded."

    old "Yeah, follow me!"
    new "Yeah, follow me!"

    old "Sarah felt Samayra take her hand. She felt her body seize up at even the light touch of the girl."
    new "Sarah felt Samayra take her hand. She felt her body seize up at even the light touch of the girl."

    old "Samayra began to pull her along and Sarah felt her body jolt into motion."
    new "Samayra began to pull her along and Sarah felt her body jolt into motion."

    old "Running out the door, Sarah tried to keep up with Samayra."
    new "Running out the door, Sarah tried to keep up with Samayra."

    old "The girl's feet moved with a swiftness she'd rarely seen from her."
    new "The girl's feet moved with a swiftness she'd rarely seen from her."

    old "All around them, the city bustled with the Lethram nightlife. People all around them, living ordinary lives."
    new "All around them, the city bustled with the Lethram nightlife. People all around them, living ordinary lives."

    old "Running down the street along with Samayra, Sarah could almost imagine herself doing the same."
    new "Running down the street along with Samayra, Sarah could almost imagine herself doing the same."

    old "The girl dragged her through streets and twisting alleys until they suddenly emerged onto a busy side street."
    new "The girl dragged her through streets and twisting alleys until they suddenly emerged onto a busy side street."

    old "A crowd of men and women already stood gathered outside, busily engaged with one another."
    new "A crowd of men and women already stood gathered outside, busily engaged with one another."

    old "A sign above the bar read 'The Burly Bass'."
    new "A sign above the bar read 'The Burly Bass'."

    old "Samayra nodded and continued to pull Sarah along."
    new "Samayra nodded and continued to pull Sarah along."

    old "Yeah, come on!"
    new "Yeah, come on!"

    old "Pulling her through the mass of people, Sarah entered the bar itself."
    new "Pulling her through the mass of people, Sarah entered the bar itself."

    old "Inside, the air was warm from the burning hearth, giving it a comfortable feel."
    new "Inside, the air was warm from the burning hearth, giving it a comfortable feel."

    old "Mounted on the wall, a fish. Likely what gave the bar it's name, Sarah concluded."
    new "Mounted on the wall, a fish. Likely what gave the bar it's name, Sarah concluded."

    old "Here's a spot!"
    new "Here's a spot!"

    old "Sarah continued to follow Samayra, finding a few empty seats near one of the many tables."
    new "Sarah continued to follow Samayra, finding a few empty seats near one of the many tables."

    old "It had been a long time since Sarah had been in a crowd like this."
    new "It had been a long time since Sarah had been in a crowd like this."

    old "Looking over the room, she was surprised to see that so many were near her and Samayra's age."
    new "Looking over the room, she was surprised to see that so many were near her and Samayra's age."

    old "The parties in Castle Reinmeer had been fun enough, but most nobles and dignitaries were significantly older."
    new "The parties in Castle Reinmeer had been fun enough, but most nobles and dignitaries were significantly older."

    old "She wasn't sure if she had ever seen so many people her own age all packed into one spot."
    new "She wasn't sure if she had ever seen so many people her own age all packed into one spot."

    old "All around her, countless small groups were engaged, each in their own conversation, lurched over a drink."
    new "All around her, countless small groups were engaged, each in their own conversation, lurched over a drink."

    old "You want to drink something?"
    new "You want to drink something?"

    old "She watched as Samayra jumped up and dissapeared into the crowd."
    new "She watched as Samayra jumped up and dissapeared into the crowd."

    old "Sarah was surprised to see just how quickly she seemed to adapt to her new environment."
    new "Sarah was surprised to see just how quickly she seemed to adapt to her new environment."

    old "Perhaps the girl would be alright after all."
    new "Perhaps the girl would be alright after all."

    old "Only a moment later, Samayra emerged back out from the mass of people, holding up two cups."
    new "Only a moment later, Samayra emerged back out from the mass of people, holding up two cups."

    old "She placed them down in front of Sarah as she sat back down."
    new "She placed them down in front of Sarah as she sat back down."

    old "They had wine or beer, so I went for wine."
    new "They had wine or beer, so I went for wine."

    old "That's great. About all I was used to drinking back in Rosanna."
    new "That's great. About all I was used to drinking back in Rosanna."

    old "Samayra took one sip, then she grimaced."
    new "Samayra took one sip, then she grimaced."

    old "What? No good?"
    new "What? No good?"

    old "Well it's...different..."
    new "Well it's...different..."

    old "Well, I don't think they serve the quality stuff you're used to."
    new "Well, I don't think they serve the quality stuff you're used to."

    old "She watched as Samayra forced herself to take another drink."
    new "She watched as Samayra forced herself to take another drink."

    old "This time, her face remained more stoic."
    new "This time, her face remained more stoic."

    old "It's...I'll learn to love it, I'm sure."
    new "It's...I'll learn to love it, I'm sure."

    old "Despite the girl's frail appearance, she had a persevering nature."
    new "Despite the girl's frail appearance, she had a persevering nature."

    old "Perhaps they had that in common too."
    new "Perhaps they had that in common too."

    old "So, when do they start-"
    new "So, when do they start-"

    old "Suddenly a loud clapping noise could be heard."
    new "Suddenly a loud clapping noise could be heard."

    old "All at once, everyone went silent."
    new "All at once, everyone went silent."

    old "Sarah turned her head to look at the man. A rather large and fat, but seemingly very happy, man stood out in the center of the room."
    new "Sarah turned her head to look at the man. A rather large and fat, but seemingly very happy, man stood out in the center of the room."

    old "Next to him, his equally well-fed and happy wife."
    new "Next to him, his equally well-fed and happy wife."

    old "Barkeeper\" \"Ladies, gentlemen, welcome to tonight's monthly Lower-Ward dance."
    new "Barkeeper\" \"Ladies, gentlemen, welcome to tonight's monthly Lower-Ward dance."

    old "The Lower-Ward, out near the docks. Not the best part of town, but far from the worst. Working people most of all."
    new "The Lower-Ward, out near the docks. Not the best part of town, but far from the worst. Working people most of all."

    old "Barkeeper\" \"The theme of tonight is music from the Union Kingdoms. We have a great band from former Rosanna, give them all a coin if you can spare it."
    new "Barkeeper\" \"The theme of tonight is music from the Union Kingdoms. We have a great band from former Rosanna, give them all a coin if you can spare it."

    old "Sarah looked at a small group of musicians near the back of the room."
    new "Sarah looked at a small group of musicians near the back of the room."

    old "Former Rosanna he had said. Not surprising, after the fall, everyone that wasn't enslaved had become a refugee."
    new "Former Rosanna he had said. Not surprising, after the fall, everyone that wasn't enslaved had become a refugee."

    old "Rosannan's made their fortune whichever way they now could, wandering the world. Music was a decent way, if one had the skill."
    new "Rosannan's made their fortune whichever way they now could, wandering the world. Music was a decent way, if one had the skill."

    old "Barkeeper\" \"Basic dances, nothin fancy. We swap up solo dances and partner dances, keep to the rules, and everyone is gonna have a good time."
    new "Barkeeper\" \"Basic dances, nothin fancy. We swap up solo dances and partner dances, keep to the rules, and everyone is gonna have a good time."

    old "Barkeeper\" \"Cause trouble, and well, you gonna have to deal with my dear wife here."
    new "Barkeeper\" \"Cause trouble, and well, you gonna have to deal with my dear wife here."

    old "Some in the crowd hollered, causing laughter."
    new "Some in the crowd hollered, causing laughter."

    old "Barkeeper\" \"She may look nice, but she used to work the fish gutting houses, so she ain't got no trouble guttin on of ya'll."
    new "Barkeeper\" \"She may look nice, but she used to work the fish gutting houses, so she ain't got no trouble guttin on of ya'll."

    old "More laughter from the crowd."
    new "More laughter from the crowd."

    old "Barkeeper\" \"Well, with that said, let's get this started."
    new "Barkeeper\" \"Well, with that said, let's get this started."

    old "The barkeeper slammed his fist on the table, and on cue, the band began to play."
    new "The barkeeper slammed his fist on the table, and on cue, the band began to play."

    old "Before Sarah even understood what had happened, the dancing floor had begun to fill up."
    new "Before Sarah even understood what had happened, the dancing floor had begun to fill up."

    old "The first song she instantly recognized, an old song most everyone from Rosanna learned. A summer harvesting song."
    new "The first song she instantly recognized, an old song most everyone from Rosanna learned. A summer harvesting song."

    old "Hey? What's wrong, you don't like it?"
    new "Hey? What's wrong, you don't like it?"

    old "Sarah felt Samayra's hand on her shoulder."
    new "Sarah felt Samayra's hand on her shoulder."

    old "Your face."
    new "Your face."

    old "Sarah reached up and touched her face. Stained with tears. How had she not realized it."
    new "Sarah reached up and touched her face. Stained with tears. How had she not realized it."

    old "She pulled her sleeves past her face, clearing away the tears."
    new "She pulled her sleeves past her face, clearing away the tears."

    old "Ooh, no it's nothing. Just, the song...I know it from when I grew up. Memories I guess."
    new "Ooh, no it's nothing. Just, the song...I know it from when I grew up. Memories I guess."

    old "She felt Samayra suddenly hug her."
    new "She felt Samayra suddenly hug her."

    old "It's alright, Sarah. I get sad sometimes, you can too."
    new "It's alright, Sarah. I get sad sometimes, you can too."

    old "Sarah patted Samayra's arms."
    new "Sarah patted Samayra's arms."

    old "Sure, but tonight should be about having fun."
    new "Sure, but tonight should be about having fun."

    old "Together, the two watched the crowd that had taken to the dance floor."
    new "Together, the two watched the crowd that had taken to the dance floor."

    old "Their steps were quick but untrained."
    new "Their steps were quick but untrained."

    old "However, despite any lack of formal training, it didn't seem wrong. Rather, it seemed all the more natural and energetic."
    new "However, despite any lack of formal training, it didn't seem wrong. Rather, it seemed all the more natural and energetic."

    old "Each moved according with the other, in a rhythm that likely came from plenty of practice."
    new "Each moved according with the other, in a rhythm that likely came from plenty of practice."

    old "As the first song drew to an end, a second was quickly set in."
    new "As the first song drew to an end, a second was quickly set in."

    old "Observing the movements of the crowd, Sarah and Samayra each quickly figured out all the many spoken and unspoken rules of the dance."
    new "Observing the movements of the crowd, Sarah and Samayra each quickly figured out all the many spoken and unspoken rules of the dance."

    old "Couples and solo dancers stood on opposite ends of the rooms, gathered around the edge of the dance floor."
    new "Couples and solo dancers stood on opposite ends of the rooms, gathered around the edge of the dance floor."

    old "Whenever a song ended, those on the floor made way for new dancers stepping in from the side."
    new "Whenever a song ended, those on the floor made way for new dancers stepping in from the side."

    old "Round and round, the crowd managed its own informal system of swapping people in and out."
    new "Round and round, the crowd managed its own informal system of swapping people in and out."

    old "By the time the fifth song came around, Sarah saw Samayra jump up."
    new "By the time the fifth song came around, Sarah saw Samayra jump up."

    old "Whatever courage possessed the girl, Sarah would never know."
    new "Whatever courage possessed the girl, Sarah would never know."

    old "She watched as Samayra made her way towards the crowd, taking her place among the other waiting dancers."
    new "She watched as Samayra made her way towards the crowd, taking her place among the other waiting dancers."

    old "When the song ended and her turn came up she rushed onto the dance floor."
    new "When the song ended and her turn came up she rushed onto the dance floor."

    old "Sarah craned her neck, trying to keep track of Samayra."
    new "Sarah craned her neck, trying to keep track of Samayra."

    old "For a brief moment, she lost her in frenzy of the people swapping in and out."
    new "For a brief moment, she lost her in frenzy of the people swapping in and out."

    old "Then, she saw her."
    new "Then, she saw her."

    old "If she hadn't known any better, she might have almost imagined it was an entirely different girl standing there."
    new "If she hadn't known any better, she might have almost imagined it was an entirely different girl standing there."

    old "Gone were all the small signs of her awkwardness and nervousness."
    new "Gone were all the small signs of her awkwardness and nervousness."

    old "Instead, her body now stood poised and fixed. Her expression, calm focus."
    new "Instead, her body now stood poised and fixed. Her expression, calm focus."

    old "For a moment, she held the pose like a statue."
    new "For a moment, she held the pose like a statue."

    old "Those around her, until now acceptable, suddenly seemed amateur by comparison."
    new "Those around her, until now acceptable, suddenly seemed amateur by comparison."

    old "Then the music began anew."
    new "Then the music began anew."

    old "Though the song was again from the Union Kingdoms, and the dance steps an odd mixture of that and Lethram, Samayra navigated it all."
    new "Though the song was again from the Union Kingdoms, and the dance steps an odd mixture of that and Lethram, Samayra navigated it all."

    old "Sarah watched in awe as Samayra easily matched the style of the others. If anything, she outdid them."
    new "Sarah watched in awe as Samayra easily matched the style of the others. If anything, she outdid them."

    old "The steps were quicker. Swifter than perhaps tradition in Bagrad."
    new "The steps were quicker. Swifter than perhaps tradition in Bagrad."

    old "Sarah watched as Samayra easily matched their speed, her body twisting to the rhythm of the music."
    new "Sarah watched as Samayra easily matched their speed, her body twisting to the rhythm of the music."

    old "Her dress flowed behind her, tracing her ever movement."
    new "Her dress flowed behind her, tracing her ever movement."

    old "And though it all looked chaotic, Sarah could see that Samayra was entirely under control."
    new "And though it all looked chaotic, Sarah could see that Samayra was entirely under control."

    old "Even as she spun her body around again, she carefully avoided anyone else, moving in between them, constantly adjusting."
    new "Even as she spun her body around again, she carefully avoided anyone else, moving in between them, constantly adjusting."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah could see Samayra nearly rush into another girl."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah could see Samayra nearly rush into another girl."

    old "But rather than an actual clash, the two easily adjusted and adapted their performance to each other."
    new "But rather than an actual clash, the two easily adjusted and adapted their performance to each other."

    old "Suddenly the two were dancing together, their steps appearing planned and trained, though entirely incidental."
    new "Suddenly the two were dancing together, their steps appearing planned and trained, though entirely incidental."

    old "The tempo of the music build and with it the fevered speed of their movements."
    new "The tempo of the music build and with it the fevered speed of their movements."

    old "Sarah watched with awe as Samayra's body bend towards impossible angles."
    new "Sarah watched with awe as Samayra's body bend towards impossible angles."

    old "How her entire body turned around on as little as the tips of her toes."
    new "How her entire body turned around on as little as the tips of her toes."

    old "Her flushed face, giddy with excitement at doing what she did best."
    new "Her flushed face, giddy with excitement at doing what she did best."

    old "In a brief moment, Sarah caught herself being jealous of the random strange girl that had caught Samayra's eye if only for one dance."
    new "In a brief moment, Sarah caught herself being jealous of the random strange girl that had caught Samayra's eye if only for one dance."

    old "Then, the last note was struck."
    new "Then, the last note was struck."

    old "All at once, each of the dancers finished."
    new "All at once, each of the dancers finished."

    old "Those waiting rushed in, those done dancing, rushed out. A frenzied melee."
    new "Those waiting rushed in, those done dancing, rushed out. A frenzied melee."

    old "Sarah saw Samayra pop out of the crowd."
    new "Sarah saw Samayra pop out of the crowd."

    old "She sat back down, nearly falling onto the chair."
    new "She sat back down, nearly falling onto the chair."

    old "Wow, you were amazing."
    new "Wow, you were amazing."

    old "Sarah could see Samayra's chest rise and fall from her fast breathing."
    new "Sarah could see Samayra's chest rise and fall from her fast breathing."

    old "You...you really think so?"
    new "You...you really think so?"

    old "It wasn't even a white lie, she'd really been incredible."
    new "It wasn't even a white lie, she'd really been incredible."

    old "Samayra was smiling more than Sarah had seen since she left Bagrad."
    new "Samayra was smiling more than Sarah had seen since she left Bagrad."

    old "I'm out of shape though...just one round and I'm already tired."
    new "I'm out of shape though...just one round and I'm already tired."

    old "Could also just be this place. And how they dance. It's not exactly how you or I was taught growing up."
    new "Could also just be this place. And how they dance. It's not exactly how you or I was taught growing up."

    old "Samayra grabbed her cup and downed it entirely."
    new "Samayra grabbed her cup and downed it entirely."

    old "She slammed the cup back down with surprising force."
    new "She slammed the cup back down with surprising force."

    old "I'm gonna go again!"
    new "I'm gonna go again!"

    old "Before Sarah could say anything, Samayra rushed back in."
    new "Before Sarah could say anything, Samayra rushed back in."

    old "Watching the girl from a distance, her performance as well as her stamina proved endlessly surprising."
    new "Watching the girl from a distance, her performance as well as her stamina proved endlessly surprising."

    old "Round by round, the girl participated."
    new "Round by round, the girl participated."

    old "Over time, Sarah could see she wasn't the only one watching Samayra."
    new "Over time, Sarah could see she wasn't the only one watching Samayra."

    old "Her performance and unusual dress for Lethram society, made her stand out."
    new "Her performance and unusual dress for Lethram society, made her stand out."

    old "All around the room, men, women, seemed to be eying her. For her part, the girl herself didn't seem to much notice."
    new "All around the room, men, women, seemed to be eying her. For her part, the girl herself didn't seem to much notice."

    old "Sarah heard the song die down."
    new "Sarah heard the song die down."

    old "Samayra rushed up to the edge of the dance floor, but rather than return, she began to wave."
    new "Samayra rushed up to the edge of the dance floor, but rather than return, she began to wave."

    old "Sarah eyed her for a moment, though she already knew what the girl wanted."
    new "Sarah eyed her for a moment, though she already knew what the girl wanted."

    old "Sarah! Come dance with me!"
    new "Sarah! Come dance with me!"

    old "Sarah put the cup down and got up. If she didn't go dance, she'd never hear the end of it."
    new "Sarah put the cup down and got up. If she didn't go dance, she'd never hear the end of it."

    old "Slowly she weaved her way through the crowd until she came upon Samayra."
    new "Slowly she weaved her way through the crowd until she came upon Samayra."

    old "I don't know this dance."
    new "I don't know this dance."

    old "That's fine, I'll lead!"
    new "That's fine, I'll lead!"

    old "Sarah felt Samayra grab her hand and pull her onto the dance floor."
    new "Sarah felt Samayra grab her hand and pull her onto the dance floor."

    old "Before she knew it, Sarah saw she was surrounded by people on all sides. Waiting for the music to start."
    new "Before she knew it, Sarah saw she was surrounded by people on all sides. Waiting for the music to start."

    old "It took her a moment to realize everyone wasn't just standing there."
    new "It took her a moment to realize everyone wasn't just standing there."

    old "They were standing in pairs."
    new "They were standing in pairs."

    old "For a brief moment, she felt embarassed to stand there alone without a partner."
    new "For a brief moment, she felt embarassed to stand there alone without a partner."

    old "Only to turn to Samayra and see the girl smiling eagerly."
    new "Only to turn to Samayra and see the girl smiling eagerly."

    old "I think this is a partner dance."
    new "I think this is a partner dance."

    old "You can be my partner, right?"
    new "You can be my partner, right?"

    old "I think it's more like a...boyfriend and girlfriend kind of idea."
    new "I think it's more like a...boyfriend and girlfriend kind of idea."

    old "She watched Samayra shrug."
    new "She watched Samayra shrug."

    old "I don't think we're short any parts we need for a dance."
    new "I don't think we're short any parts we need for a dance."

    old "Sarah felt herself go red in the face. She couldn't necessarily argue with that."
    new "Sarah felt herself go red in the face. She couldn't necessarily argue with that."

    old "If their inconvenient partnering was a problem, it didn't seem to raise much of any. The mood in the bar remained amicable."
    new "If their inconvenient partnering was a problem, it didn't seem to raise much of any. The mood in the bar remained amicable."

    old "The first notes for the song were struck."
    new "The first notes for the song were struck."

    old "All the men closed the distance with their dancing partner."
    new "All the men closed the distance with their dancing partner."

    old "Samayra in turn did the same."
    new "Samayra in turn did the same."

    old "Sarah felt Samayra's hand entwine with hers. Her other hand casually yet firmly on Sarah's lower back."
    new "Sarah felt Samayra's hand entwine with hers. Her other hand casually yet firmly on Sarah's lower back."

    old "Sarah instinctively wrapped her own hand around Samayra's waist."
    new "Sarah instinctively wrapped her own hand around Samayra's waist."

    old "A slight tremble ran through her body. To suddenly be this close to her. Her face only inches from her own."
    new "A slight tremble ran through her body. To suddenly be this close to her. Her face only inches from her own."

    old "The Samayra opposite of her was a very different creature from the girl she knew."
